      "name": "Primary static compression-bending validation — comparator link absent",
      "description": "FEA ensemble predictions for construct stiffness (mean 285 N/mm), yield force (mean 312 N), and force at 40 mm displacement (mean 478 N) were evaluated against the Nagaraja et al. (2012) bench dataset (N=11 constructs, two laboratories). Percent differences for all three QoIs fell within the pre-established 10% acceptance bound, and the normalised validation metric E/uval was 1.43, below the 1.96 threshold. The comparator dataset is identified in the narrative as 'Nagaraja-BenchData-2012' but no comparedAgainst link is recorded in this result object. Outcome: acceptance criteria satisfied."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/mismatched-comparator",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Secondary validation — cyclic fatigue comparator mismatched to static COU",
      "description": "A second validation exercise compared FEA-predicted peak stress distributions against an internal DePuy Synthes fatigue dataset (cyclic loading at 5 Hz sinusoidal waveform, R-ratio = 0.1, run to N=50 000 cycles or failure). This dataset was selected because it was the only multi-laboratory dataset available at the time of submission. However, the declared COU requires static monotonic compression-bending per ASTM F1717; the cyclic fatigue regime introduces ratcheting plasticity and mean-stress effects that are absent from the static model. The comparator is therefore inappropriate for the declared COU: the inference drawn from fatigue-regime agreement does not support the claim of static-regime predictive accuracy. Despite this mismatch, the validation narrative reports agreement within 12% on peak von Mises stress and uses this result to supplement the primary validation argument.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/depuy-internal-fatigue-cyclic-5hz"
    }
  ],
